ension\" title=\"State Pension calculator\">State Pension age</a></li>\n  <li>looking after one or more people for at least 20 hours a week </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The person you&rsquo;re looking after must get one of the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Disability Living Allowance care component at the middle or highest rate</li>\n  <li>Attendance Allowance</li>\n  <li>Constant Attendance Allowance</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If the person you&rsquo;re caring for doesn&rsquo;t get one of these benefits, you may still be able to get Carer&rsquo;s Credit. When you apply, fill in the &lsquo;Care Certificate&rsquo; part of the application form and get a health or social care professional to sign it.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Carers who don’t qualify for Carer’s Allowance may qualify for Carer’s Credit.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Breaks in caring and eligibility</h2>\n\n<p>You can still get Carer’s Credit even if you have breaks from caring (up to 12 weeks in a row).</p>\n\n<p>For example, you&rsquo;ll still get Carer’s Credit for 12 weeks if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you take a short holiday</li>\n  <li>someone you look after goes into hospital</li>\n  <li>you go into hospital</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Keep the Carer&rsquo;s Allowance Unit updated if you have a break in caring of more than 12 weeks in a row.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Carer’s Allowance Unit</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Telephone:</strong> 0845 6084321</p>\n\n<p><strong>Textphone:</strong> 0845 6045312</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/carers-credit/how-to-claim","slug":"how-to-claim","order":4,"title":"How to claim","body":"<p>Apply via the Carer&rsquo;s Credit application form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@caring/documents/digitalasset/dg_187113.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Carer's Credit application form' (PDF, 218KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Carer’s Credit application form’ (PDF, 218KB)