-2-national-insurance.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/pay-class-2-national-insurance","title":"Pay Class 2 National Insurance contributions","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-12-11T16:06:28+00:00","details":{"need_id":"B1026","business_proposition":true,"description":"How to pay Class 2 self-employed National Insurance contributions - Direct Debit, bank, Post Office, cheque, payslips","language":"en","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>Pay your Class 2 National Insurance contributions by Direct Debit, through your bank, at the Post Office or by post.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>It’s your responsibility to make sure payments reach HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) on time. You can pay monthly or every 6 months by Direct Debit or in response to payment requests in October and April. You can also make one-off payments for any arrears you owe. </p>\n\n<h2>Direct Debit</h2>\n\n<p>To set up a Direct Debit send the Direct Debit form to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>. The address is on the form. </p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Circumstance</th>\n      <th>Form</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Starting self-employment</td>\n      <td><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/pdfs/ca5601.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Direct Debit form, CA5601' (PDF, 745KB)\">Download &lsquo;Direct Debit form, CA5601&rsquo; (PDF, 745KB)</a></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Already self-employed</td>\n      <td><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/nic/ca5611.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Direct Debit form, CA5611' (PDF, 142KB)\">Download &lsquo;Direct Debit form, CA5611&rsquo; (PDF, 142KB)</a></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Allow 21 days to set it up. <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will tell you in writing before taking the first payment.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Payments appear on your statement as